President Obama released a statement on the 10th anniversary of the beginning of the Iraq war, paying tribute to the service members and civilians who served and sacrificed during the conflict. He honored the memory of the Americans who lost their lives and expressed gratitude to military families. The President highlighted the ongoing commitment to supporting those who were wounded and improving treatment for traumatic brain injury and post-traumatic stress disorder. He emphasized the importance of helping veterans pursue education and find employment. President Obama drew strength and inspiration from these American patriots who exemplify the values of courage, selflessness, and teamwork.